com.sjanarth.dsutils

Class BasicObjectWithProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sjanarth.dsutils.BasicObjectWithProperties
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BasicTrie, BasicTrie.BasicTrieNode

    public class BasicObjectWithProperties
extends Object
    A simple object class with associated properties that are modelled as key/value pairs. The values associated with the properties could be of primitive types or standard java collection classes or any valid java class. If the values are of a type that inherits from java.util.Collection, this implementation automatically appends the new values to the existing values without having to explicitly do so.
    See Also:
    addProperty for more info.

      • addProperty

        public void addProperty(Object key,
                        Object value)
        Adds a given value to a property identified by the key.
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the property whose value must be modified.
        value - the value to set the property to.

        If the property already exists and has a current value that is a java collection, this method will add the given value to the collection and not overwrite the previous values. If the property already exists and has a current value that is not a java collection, this method will create a new java.util.Set to hold the values of this property and initialize it with the both the previous and the current values. If the property does not already exist, this method will create a new java.util.Set to hold the values of this property and initialize it with the given value.
